rComments: Very well structured lectures (powerpoints always posted prompty) and very friendly at office hours. IMO, masterfully designed problem sets that make you feel like you understand the topic just by doing those questions. By far, the best-taught second year physics class this year.
Overall his lecture are pretty good and easy to follow, but if you want to do well in test better read the textbook.
lectures are clear but it takes a lot of work to apply them to the tests
Love physics because of him
So inspirational and helpful. Btw, pretty funny and approachable.
Really Funny.
My boy Joseph is so chill. He always tries to answer your questions without making you feel dumb. Really approachable, super awesome dude.

As an experimental physicist, he made the standard way too low and covered way much less than what I expect from a 2nd year student. Not really dedicated to teaching whatsoever, how I wish we can have a theorist teaching this course!
Made thermal Physics so interesting!

Good guy and good speaker. Good material and problem sets. Lecture notes would be so much more valuable if posted a day before class + a bit more context/a touch of rounder explanation instead of a sketch/lecture aid w/mostly formulas. Would also be a lot better if problem sets were posted earlier, say a week before due date.
Great speaker. Always approachable. Tests were fair and problem sets simple. Would take the course again!
Prof. Thywissen is one of the best lecturers on the UofT campus in my opinion. But then again, his course, PHY252, was hard and I don't hold it against him.
Easy exams, great prof. Made thermal physics interesting!
I don't understand why people said his lectures are boring. Maybe he improved since then, because his lectures are great now: clear and interesting. He's also very approachable and helpful.

His lectures are boring. He writes equations on the board without explaining and then makes mistakes and has to erase. Wikipedia is very useful for this course, skipped every class yet managed an A+ cuz of wiki(at least no mistakes there). Going to extra help is useless too, he just tells you to read the solutions then kicks you out of his office.
Quite helpful and approachable if you do ask for help and work hard

provides clear explanations w/ very organized notes and demonstrations!!
